results.name: Number of n-digit right-truncatable primes in base 16.
comment: See A237600 for a complete list of right-truncatable primes in base 16.
link: Stanislav Sykora, PARI/GP scripts for genetic threads
example: a(2)=16 because there are 16 right truncatable hex numbers with two hex digits: 25,29,2B,2F,35,3B,3D,53,59,71,7F,B3,B5,BF,D3,DF.
program: (PARI) See the link (use GT_DivMod0 with arguments "isprime" for "property" and 16 for "b").
results.author: _Stanislav Sykora_, Feb 15 2014
